metatags.og:description:
Co-Founder at Medmonk · With over 15 years of pharmacy experience and a Doctorate in Pharmaceutical Sciences, Somaira Punjwani is dedicated to improving patient access to care. Formerly a lead pharmacist at Walgreens, she specialized in HIV, Oncology, Rheumatoid Arthritis, and Hepatitis therapies. 

At Walgreens, Somaira developed a co-pay assistance process, which was later adopted nationwide. This innovation led her to co-found Medmonk, a technology-driven platform offering comprehensive support for complex chronic rare diseases.

Somaira's expertise and dedication to patient care are instrumental in driving the creation of solutions that enhance patient and provider experiences. Her strong leadership ensures that patients receive the necessary support for life-saving treatments, further underscoring her commitment to improving patient access to care. · Experience: Medmonk · Location: Greater Sacramento · 8 connections on LinkedIn.
